reviewText: We have really enjoyed watching these movies. Saw the second part last year on Cartoon Network ordered the set and they have quickly become our favorite Halloween movies... Used both at a birthday party as the movie part and all the kids loved it so much they watched the first one several times. Definatly recommend to other buyers!!!!!

this movie reminds me of how amazing halloween was when i was little...i took this to my boyfriend's house and we watched it together on his couch....the soundtrack is excellent makeout music...left it on the menu screen for 20 minutes
The grandchildren enjoyed this followup movie to The Scary Godmother.  The movie kept a 2 and 4 year old entertained for many hours.  We had to turn off and make them go play after a while.
This is a big hit with the whole family every year around Halloween but why not enjoy it throughout the year?  It's a good time!
I love this cartoon. Its totaly awsome even better than the first one. Great family movie for all ages. Totaly worth your money and maybe even more
This is a great movie.  If you like halloween movies then you will love this one.  I can watch it all year long instead of waiting for TV to show it.

This movie is great. More fun and many more laughs. I recommend having a movie night and watching Scary Godmother Halloween Spooktacular and The Revenge of Jimmy. Both movies are now a Halloween tradtion. Great fun for all ages and even us big kids at heart. I love how Hannah saves Halloween in this one. As Scary Godmother would say, "Happy Halloween To All, And To All A Good Fright!"
My 8 and 6 year old have watched this several times. I think that it is a good sequel to the first movie.

Happy Halloween Amazon customers. This movie is great. My friends and I love the movie and always like to copy parts (like Skully having money in his "other pelvis"). Our favorite part was where Harry loses his signature shirt and even though they censor it you clearly see his body. I think Bert, Darrel, Katie, Hannah, and Jimmy have new voice actors. So I like both but this one much more. They both run for about an hour or so and the price is worth it.

My brother and I grew up excitedly waiting for this movie and the prequel to come on Cartoon Network every Halloween. At 16 and 18, we decided to order this one and I am so glad we did. We're happy to continue the tradition of watching these movies every year. The animation is fairly dated, (it came out in 2005) but it is so cute that we hardly noticed. Definitely worth the price!

A perfectly funny sequel to the first Scary Godmother Halloween Spooktacular! Kids will learn a valuable lesson that revenge is never a good option and how to have fun with friends like Hannah, Skully, Bug-A-Boo, and more! If you have the first Scary Godmother movie, you should definitely get this one to complete your collection!

This is a light hearted fun movie to watch with the entire famil. Adults and children will enjoy it. Make it a holiday tradition

Lives up to the original in quality of story and animation. My daughter loves it, and I don't mind watching it OR the original(even one after the other!) with her at all, the story works at several levels. Good for all ages.
I love the Scary Godmother books and was happy to see it in movie form. Hope to see more from this artist. Great Halloween tales that are not too scary for a little one.

this movie is great for kids and adults alike its a little simplistic for adults but its a very feel good movie. plus it teaches a good lesson at the same time it entertains. i find it very amusing even as an adult.

My children and I watch this every Halloween since the youngest was 5 years old, it has become a tradition. We moved overseas and wasn't able to get the same stations stateside. This video help us not miss out on one of our holiday traditions.

I got this collection for my daughter after we saw them on TV and she loved them. They are fun and Jimmy finally learns something at the end. The characters are endearing. These a Halloween treat for kids and adults alike.
